Eerie in the contrast of their lethal size and silent movement, ScorpionMechs are deployed on the orbital and planetside battlefield when no quarter is to be given to the enemy, and none expected.

They're colony killers.

You send them in when you want the enemy base and any feeble defenders protecting it razed to the ground.

These scuttling terrors can chop enemy armors in half in close quarters or pound them to pieces from a distance. Using a variety of modular payloads, the ScorpionMech can tailor its weapons suite to the mission, whether it be cold, quiet up-close killing, napalm and gatling cascades at ballistic distances, or missiles beyond the horizon.

This 6/8mm scale ScorpionMech can be utilized as an attack drone against 15mm or 28mm figures with ease, or utilized in any miniatures-agnostic rule set. Or just as a keychain.

This is a fused, quarter-scale version of the 28mm version. It will be at home going into combat against tiny warmachines in the 3025 era or 40000 years from now.

Saws, claws, gatlings, flamethrowers, and gun clusters are all included in this package of STL files.

Details and links are in the included PDF instructions. If you want, you can preview them here at this WeTransfer link...
https://we.tl/t-OFCeq2Rnp7

I also offer 28mm and 15mm versions of this devastating battle construct. Check my other files for those offerings.

Enjoy!

Best,
JBR

Provides a version of Woddish's excellent Tiny Tank Fancy Howitzer that has had the dozer blade removed as an alternate option. Also contains parts that are enabled to be quickly swapped and edited for customization by changing visibility of components between different options for hatches, crew, symbols/icons.

tiny 6mm scaled anti aircraft addon options for classic looking rather epic tanks, of a style you might even call an 'ancient percussive tool', matching other tiny tanks designed for the third edition of a long out of print game.

theres an somewhat original design of an anti aircraft turret wot uses bullets/flak designed to look like an older version of its more modern counterpart, and a design for a anti aircraft turret wot uses explosive missiles inspired by old metal miniatures and an addon kit that was once available on shapeways

there's also a tiny little radar dish

the rest of the tiny tank body is not included, these were made to match the style of FASIS's tiny tanks but could also be adapted to other kits

When da Big Meks gettin' tired of walkin‚Äô up to da enemy just to hit 'em, they built Shoota Botz ‚Äì walkin‚Äô fortress o‚Äô dakka designed to turn battlefields into bullet storms wiff blasta beams n rokkits. Bristlin' with barrels, belchin' smoke, and covered in rivets, dis bot‚Äôs idea of a good time is shootin‚Äô everything that moves... and then shootin‚Äô it again, just to be sure.

From rokkits to rattlin‚Äô big shootas or ork tek blastas, Shoota Botz got more guns than sense ‚Äì which is just how da greenskins lovin' it. No choppy arms here, just pure ranged firepower, rainin‚Äô lead from across da field while laughin‚Äô like a mad git.

Note: Dis is a fan-made model, full of grimy character and orkiness, but not linked to any official game or company. It‚Äôs just for da ladz who like loud machines an‚Äô big fights.

This model is compatible to the bitz of following models:
- Mosha Bot
- Brawla Bot


======= PRINTING =========

- Layer hight 0.05mm
- Use tree / organic supports.
- I printed my test prints with a 0.25mm nozzle (for best quality)
- Orientate the Exhausts01-04 vertical

======= Assembly =========

If you need instructions - just open all files in 3D Builder or e.g. Meshmixer at the same time (drag and drop). There you can have a look where they need to go in 3D.



---
Shame less beggin' for some coins for caffeine I need doin' stuff like that :-)

Please consider a tip ....this highly detailed model was a work of hundeds of hours of free time!
If you do so, I HIGHLY APPRECIATE YOUR GENEROSITY :-)

Kind regands,
Tersus

Despite everything our dedicated team of tiny engineeres continues to push forward in the field of tiny military transportation. Our latest offering is the fresh addition of two self-propelled artillery systems. These fully enclosed machines are perfect for any army - whether you desire to lob shells from afar or blast enemy strogpoints at point blank range.

This vehicle is perfect for any games involving tiny tanks or robots in 6 to 8mm scale.

There is a new terror stalking the arenas and battlefields of Junctionworld and its worldgate networks.

Eerie in the contrast of their lethal size and silent movement, ScorpionMechs are sent through hostile interdimensional portals as shock attack units, scything and slicing through any resistance on the other side.

In the Gatekeepers' colosseums of mechanized bloodsport, ScorpionMechs have quickly earned a reputation as close-quarter killers, their tail weapons well-placed to send a buzzsaw or energized claw into an opponent's cockpit, regardless of shielding.

In conventional fights, the scuttling nightmares are sometimes inserted on to the a planetside battlefield via the use of a-grav or chemical rocket packs bolted under their hulls.

They are utilized when no quarter is to be given to the enemy, and none expected.

They're colony killers. Merciless reapers. Harvesters of those foolish enough to try and face them.

Using a variety of modular payloads, the ScorpionMech pilot can tailor their unit's weapons suite to the mission, whether it be cold, quiet up-close killing, napalm and gatling cascades at ballistic distances, or missiles from beyond the horizon.

The base package for the 15mm (I use 1/100th scale) ScorpionMech includes pincers, saws, Asher claws (named for Neal Asher, whose books you should really check out), gatlings, flamethrowers, and gun clusters. Supplemental mounts are provided for heavy cannons and missile launchers.
As mentioned above, orbital assault belly packs are also included.

This is a pretty decent undertaking, not for the faint-hearted. Rest assured, though, the largest piece (the main hull) will fit in a Mars 2 or similar-sized printer.

Details and links are in the included PDF instructions. If you want, you can preview them here at this WeTransfer link. Some steps can be skipped, since the parts are pre-fused as you get smaller and smaller...
https://we.tl/t-UHLrtY3rjL

If you've read this far, thank you. Enter LOWKEY20 at checkout for 20% off.

Or, join my Patreon at www.patreon.com/johnbearross to get a 50% rolling discount on my entire inventory.

Enjoy!

Best,
JBR

Is this a serious release? Not really... Since so many of my 0.2mm nozzles on my Bambu A1 were failing, I thought maybe one could upcycle these as weapons in tanks. Happy Orktober! This final Orktober release combines some of the previous releases into one big print-paint&play army for grimdark future. 3000 Points of pure metal, all models having tough and a high defense, so if your enemy doesn't have that much deadly or armor penetration, you'd probably have a good time!

I once played this army online in my free wargaming simulator ( https://udos3dworld.com/WargamingSimulator/ ) against some lust daemons and seriously, it was a massacre, so my opponent resigned after round 2. I included all the assets you need to play this army, so you could just use the "Upload Whole Army" feature, and have everything added to the battlefield.

This file is another remix/remaster of a file made by [TheDude21](https://www.thingiverse.com/thedude21/designs) (check him out and give him a tip, if you like). Much like the previous Glade-S, I very much liked the core Cyberpunk stylings of this vehicle concept and thought that it would make a nice adaption into a 'lower' tech level universe setting as a civilian hovercraft vehicle at the 6mm scale setting.

**About the Design.** Despite the superficial resemblance's to the original design, this project actually took quite a lot of time to remaster, because I wanted to remove as many of the 'hard-angle' edges as possible. This should make the model much better to orientate for supports and 3D print on a resin system. (zoom right in on the file to compare it with the original, if you like!)

**Other Designs.** This model set is intended to be compatible with the other 6mm (true-scale) and Hex(33) (hex scale) SciFi terrain sets that I have released on [Cults 3D](https://cults3d.com/en/users/Shiaic3D/creations) and other locations, [GumRoad](https://shiaic3d.gumroad.com/), [Printables](https://www.printables.com/@Shiaic3D/models) and [Thingiverse](https://www.thingiverse.com/shiaic1/designs).

Please search my other designs for more models of a similar type and theme.

Available for deployment!

Even if some deride it for it's seeming lack of firepower, heavy mortar carrier forms a vital part of many an imperial army. Quick and accurate it can launch prompt and precise bombardments in close cooperation with frontline troops. 

The same chassis is also utilized for a family of recon and command vehicles. These open-topped vehicles make great use of chassis' powerful engines to perform reconnaissance and patrol tasks.

These stls allow you to add heavy mortar carrier, recon tank or a command vehicle to your tiny (around 8mm) grimdark forces. Unlike previous releases this one designed for a track units (along with some hull details) to be printed as separate parts to improve printing and allow for addition of more variants down the line. So far some variants are included with track guards and variants of vehicle hulls. Recon and command tanks can be printed with their interior covered with tarp if you are not feeling like painting the interiors. Command tank includes both heavy flamethrower and heavy gyrojet as it's main weapons. In addition a mine clearing device and two variants of sideskirt armour are included for further customization. I also plan on adding some more cosmetic variants and accessories for these in the future. 

Finally, apologies for a long wait, hopefully I can pick up pace going forwards.

UPDATE 11.04.2024 - fixed undersides of the trackunits to sit flat added a dozer blade to accessories

UPDATE 05.11.2024 - fixed an issue with tracks that failed to adhere to the the trackunit under some circumstances as pointed out to me.

UPDATE 15.03.2025 - reworked track units in preparation for the new releases on this chassis to hopefully solve the issues for good. Added a new version with quarter track guards + versions without decorations on hatch for those pesky renegades while I was at it

Rumbling forward on heavy tracks, the tanks of the Imperial Army are capable of decimating enemy forces with overwhelming firepower. The versatile main battle tank is capable of being adapted to feature a wide range of alternate patterns - support vehicles capable of hauling damaged vehicles or artillery, hulls with sponsons, dozer blades and ram bars.

This is a single hull sample of a set of tank hulls featuring 8 base hull designs - The full set contains a Destroyer hull, Thunderer hull, Flamer hull, laser cannon hull, heavy bolt hull, automatic cannon hull, and two support variant hulls. Each of these come with bulldozer blade and ram bar options. Each of the standard tank hull designs also comes with options for two different sponson designs (square and inset versions) , with holes for magnetisation. Included in the main set are also two turret options, to create complete tanks. For a sample turret, please see my other designs.

This sample hull has been made to be compatible with 8mm scale main line battle tanks of the Imperial Army in a recently released 8mm grim-dark future wargame. They feature a magnet hole, and a peg compatible with existing plastic model turrets.

This sample is free. For the full set, I've priced it cheaply, but priced it as a reflection of the time I took to create such an extensive set. I deeply appreciate all those who support and encourage my work by buying any of my paid designs.

Please see my other items for a free sample of this set, and a range of other 8mm scale and other wargames and hobby models, including a set of compatible turret options for these tanks. I am an enthusiastic amateur designer, self and video-tutorial taught, so am always open to constructive feedback.

Please consider liking the design and posting a make.

This is a set of tank turrets featuring 15 weapon options, plus two with additional coaxial cannons, making a total of 17 weapon load outs. Each of those comes with optional designs, making this set of over 60 STLs!

These have been made to be compatible with 8mm scale main line battle tanks of the Imperial Army in a recently released 8mm grim-dark future wargame. They feature a magnet hole, and a peg compatible with existing plastic model hulls. The 'open hatch' designs (usually noted as designs A or C) fit the plastic hatch options for the same main battle tank, allowing for use of spare bits and personalisation. Options B and D usually feature build-in closed hatches for those who want to keep things simple. There are also two slightly different desings, allowing for some variety in turret apperance (A and B are design 1, C and D design 2) as well as designs with fuel barrels or energy generators.

The family of turretless tanks was intially envisioned as a carrier for a powerful laser weaponry. However, attrition adn loss of knowledge often meant that contructing replacement lasers was often out of question. Thus the expedient field conversion utilizing a siege cannon was born.

These stls allow you to add either a laser armed Jagdpanzer or siege cannon toting StuG to your quarter scale armies. Both vehicles come with options for trackguards as well as open commander cupolas (Sword rattling figures had to be sourced separately at this moment).

UPDATE 09/05/2024 - remade trackunit/hull separation to fit the latest iteraation of my tiny mbt for ease of printing and compatibility with future accessories. Added heavy stubber option (tis a small boy be carefull when printing)

Ok, so there are many ways to confiture the Malc, so here are a few of them. I did variants based on the combinations of the mainguns (Vanquisher, Battle Cannon, and Double LasCans with 3 different hull guns (lascanon, HvyBolter, Demolisher) and the 2 different sponsons of Autocannons and LasCans.

These STLs have been painstakingly repaired/ filled and then had the underneath scooped out to reduce suction.

Now, if the one you are seeking doesn't quite exist, just open them into 3D builder and cut/paste to your hearts desire. Its pretty easy - plenty of tutorials on the tube of YOU.

These models are all ultimately based on Danny_Cyanide's work. They were reduced in scale and assembled by Korgaan, but had a lot of internal hollow (especially around the sides/ tracks) that needed to be filled. I did a ton of repair work. Other creators have worked on these prior, but I noticed there were still internal hollows, so the ones here should be a better print with a lower chance of resin leakage - it is difficult to take multi-part STLs and assemble a single print model without some stuff missed - so this is not in any way a criticism of those fine works.

There are 8 tanks here:
BattleTurret with AutoCannonSpn and HvyBolterHull
BattleTurret with LasCannonSpn and HvyBolterHull
BattleTurret with LasCannonSpn and DemolisherHull
DblLasCaneTurret with LasCannonSpn and DemolisherHull
DblLasCaneTurret with LasCannonSpn and HvyBolterHull
DblLasCaneTurret with LasCannonSpn and LascanonHull
VanqTurret with LasCannonSpn and DemolisherHull
VanqTurret with LasCannonSpn and LascanonHull

This posting is not in anyway an invite for "aktually - sniff - blah blah blah" type of comments. People that think that way are typically not the subject matter experts they want to be on the internets. Either get off the internet or if you can do it better - do it.

https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/y-orc-battle-lorries-8mm-scale/comments#comment-answer-734601

I did these a couple of years ago so I may have forgotten someone's bits: please let me know if so. I'm a bit of a noob with MeshMixer so, again, apologies if for anything messy. I've basically embedded guns in the front, added peg-turrets and given lots of glyph/no glyph [clean] options. They've all printed fine my end so fingers crossed yours. If you have problems with the pegs not fitting the holes properly then just resize the turrets a bit as some resins cure with odd dimensions. These are re-sized to what I think orks should roughly be on the Moonjammy scale (so 90% of Vohvel's originals)? Hope you enjoy using them to munch humies. Waaagh!

UPDATE: 2023-10-11
I didn't expect quite so many downloads so to I've done some extra bits last night that I was going to leave till Christmas. Essentially just some fiddling to create more variety (orks don't really do 'standardised', do they :) ). More glyph options (the numbers correlate with those in JayMull420's pack for those wanting to fiddle more), some new turrets and, crucially, bolted versions of the dozer glyphs in addition to the welded. Hope you enjoy them and any donations to the originators listed above, please, rather than me. Cheers.

Simply Shift+Click the pieces you want to use and select export under the FILE dropdown menu. Alternatively, parts can be assembled via 3dBuilder or another software of your choice. Exported pieces are then ready for repair in netfab/3dbuilder/prusaslicer and slicing.

I have always been a big fan of the stealers of genetics from a popular board game set on a drifting, abandoned hulk in space, especially the early plastic ones with the humped back and ribbed muscles. I first came across them as soul stealers for the now OOP game Space Crusade.

I've also always wanted to do larger, warrior variants, compatible with space bugs from the world's most popular grim-dark tabletop wargame. So I've sculpted one - my first real organic sculpt. Still learning, but this has been a fun project. Fits with standard xenos warrior bits.

This file is only the torso. Pictured bits are for illustrative purposes only.

You can download compatible heads here: https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/soul-stealer-warrior-head-bit

The Empire of Sentient Man cannot reclaim constant victories over space elves who constantly terrorize human realms. But this doesn‚Äôt mean they cannot beat the foe in local skirmishes. The local victories provided to imperials limited weapon exhibits to examine. Besides many elven hover vehicles with controversial fusion of organic and greebled shaped apparatus, defenders of man had found many weapons considered by logics of military art. Some hover tank platoons are followed by self-propelled anti-aircraft engines based on the same platform. They got different names, but the Red Militia called them Zeus. The alternate name was provided due to role similar to small multilaser flak cannons the militia operate.

This model is a turret required for building self-propelled anti-aircraft based on Tiny Space Elves - Beam Hover Tank by Lord_Chronos (https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/tiny-space-elves-beam-hover-tank)

This is a remix of the attached Triceratops model mixed with the Ewok Catapult (https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4773367). I modeled the ammo bags and ropes for the catapult, as well as the leather strapping and harnesses, and enhanced the detail of everything in Zbrush. The triceratops' pose was adjusted slightly to get the catapult to not bang into his frill.

I sized this for a 40x80mm base for Hordes of the Things/ Fantasy Rules! (yes the ! is part of the name). I left the harness option in for people who want to risk printing it at it's current size, or who may want to embiggen it for display or to make a huge 28mm scale model. This one is sized roughly for my 10mm mass battle lizardman army.

When building Gore Krusha Mega Walkers, greenskin Meks sometimes opt to build massive klanky klaws as melee weapons instead of the often-seen giant saws.


FOR BEST QUALITY PRINT, PLEASE READ ALL(!) OF BELOW:

This highly detailed Klaw Arm is compatible to my Gore Krusha's Mega Walker
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/gore-krusha-mega-walker

I REALLY recommend a layer high of 0.050 or lower for all parts to get the quality I intended.
Please see the pics of my print, those are all in FDM (0,05mm layer height)!

I tried to keep the need of tree supports low, but I recommend it to use them on some parts - decide for yourself & make sure to set the tree support z-distance to a multiple of 2 (layer height) for optimal removal (keep in mind: layer height 0.05 to 0.075(!) )


----------------------------------------------------------------------
-------------- EXCEPTIONAL 'fings for this model: --------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------

---------- MOVABLE PARTS ----------
- Most pivot points are actually functional, pose the arm as you want!
- I have included a functional hydraulics option for the klaw, so it can move once assembled.
 -> You need a well calibrated printer to get this hydraulics working. Print all *FlexHydraulics*.stl with wallcount = e.g. 99 to get a massive print without infill.
 -> For the FlexHydraulics pins you need to cut of ca. 10mm of regular 1,75mm filament. (I did not test this in resin, but I guess you could print them)
 -> As an option to the FlexHydraulics there are two fixed versions. Have a look in the parts.
- Print all PINS with wallcount = e.g. 99 to get a massive print without infill.

---------- CABLES and WIRES ----------

KlawArm_03 Bits come with an option to glue in some wires (or filament).
If you use some 0,75mm¬≤ or 0,5mm¬≤ electrical wires the arm could still be movable :)

---------- Arm on the LEFT or RIGHT? ----------
You can print all parts normally except the shoulder pauldrons. (because of the flat printing side)
-> You have to mirror both pauldrons if you want the arm on the left side of your model (from your point of view)

---------- ASSEMBLY ----------

If you need instructions - just open all files in 3D Builder or e.g. Meshmixer. There you can look where they need to go.

---------- FOLLOWING: ----------

Shame less beggin' for some coins for caffeine I need doin' stuff like that :-)

Please consider a tip ....this highly detailed model was a work of 80h+ of free time!
If you do so, I HIGHLY APPRECIATE YOUR GENEROSITY :-)

Tersus

An improved pattern of the M'khand Pattern Lemoine Russel Battle Tank, with improved suspension and internal layout offering more crew comfort and higher accuracy when firing on the move. Comes with all turret coxial and sponson weapon options offered at larger scales for maximum customisation.

Completed bodies, turrets and middles have 2.5x1.25mm holes for magnets. Compatible with all epic scale M'khand-pattern Lemoine Russel parts and variants. Comes with a variety of decals and effects.

The zip includes all my parts and meshmixer files. With Meshmixer (free program from Autodesk), simply Shift+Click the pieces you want to use and select export under the FILE dropdown menu. Alternatively, parts can be assembled via 3dBuilder, Blender or another software of your choice. Exported pieces are then ready for repair in netfab/3dbuilder/prusaslicer and slicing.

For best results when printing destroyed turrets, include a closed hatch with the turret, weapon and smoke to prevent a small pocket of unprinted resin.

__For printing for LIMP/AT18, increase scale to 125% when slicing__

2023-12-03: Added new options for side weapons and a builder with all my other lemoine russel variants in it.

I've never been keen on the current model for this. The older resin version was better, but better still was the late 90s version by Tim Adcock. I've tried to recreate that version but using modern Space Elf designs.

The bulk of the model is Lord Cronos's beam hover tank from here:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/tiny-space-elves-beam-hover-tank
With the hover tank turret from here:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/tiny-space-elves-hover-tank
The fins at the back of the hull are based on the ones from this model:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/sprue-eldar-hornet
The dispensers are taken from here:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/space-elf-support-quasi-classic-platform-weapons

The model is the same scale as Lord Chronos's model on which it is based. For a more traditional 6mm scale, print it scaled to 80%.

The holes in the dispenser will probably need drilling out slightly to fit onto the mounting on the turret. The models all ought to fit but in practice I found that they don't. Alternatively try merging the web spinners with the turret and printing it as one piece.

Here and there the model is quite fragile, so take care when removing supports, assembling the parts or just handling the model.

Quite a bit larger than an Imperial Baneblade, a Kill Grinda Mega Fortress is truly a fearsome idol of the brutish Ork gods:
On massive, krushin' trakks, armed with weapons capable of destroying entire hab blocks with one shot, they rumble onwards, where da fORKtress Kaptains points them to.
Only the most powerful Warbosses have 'nuff teef to pay the bestest meks to build these mega-super-heavy assault vehicles.

An IMPORTANT note for the scale :D
- Quote of an imperial agent during a massive Ork encounter on Fungusius Primus:
"Big Mek Gutgrinda once build this thing at a scale of a Baneblade (~79%).... he was KRUSHED and GRINDED brutally to deff by WAAAGHBOSS Gobba Gitkrusha's 'GORKAfORKress' (100% scale)" ;-)



----------------------------------------------------------------------
------- FOR BEST PRINT QUALITY , PLEASE READ ALL(!) OF BELOW: --------
----------------------------------------------------------------------

I REALLY recommend a layer hight of 0.075 or lower for all parts to get the quality I intended.
Please see the pics, those are all printed in FDM (<=0,075mm)!

All parts are printed without tree supports, some parts don't need supports, but please decide for your self. :)

----------------------------------------------------------------------
---------------- EXCEPTIONAL 'fings for this model: ------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------

---------- Over all printing recommendation! ----------

Many parts have a "flat surface" -> face those to the build plate. Keep in mind, the z-axies does the detailed job!
Detailed sides / most visible sides should be faced towards the cooling fan.

The supa gattla can fit two 5x3mm magnet to be rotatable. The "KillGindaMegaFortress_SupaGattla_Pin.stl" does a similar job, but not as good, I guess... although I never tested the magnets.

The main gun can be assembled in 3 ways:
- Mega Zzappa
- Nukular Shell (with or without spacer, as you like)
- None of both

I printed the supa gattla ammo without a raft, but if you have problems with adhesion, use a raft.
-> If you have concerns about the sharp corners of the ammo belt in FMD, you have the right feeling, but "in the end it doesn't matter", you will not see this issue after assembly.
-> enable "print thin walls" in cura or equivalent in your slicer.

Arrange the lobbas ("KillGrindaMegaFortress_Lobbas02 - 07 & _LazerMarker) as you like, view all files in e.g. 3D Builder or Meshmixer to see how I designed them. The "Lazer sight"-bit is optional, you can replace it with an additional lobba as you like.

---------- Assembly ----------

All parts have a arritation point, so just "move" them until they snap or feel right.
- If you need instructions: just open all files in 3D Builder or e.g. Meshmixer. There you can look where all parts belong to.


---------- FOLLOWING: ----------

Want to fire some flesh eatin' short range artillery ammunishun that's not a bug?? Rukka Buggys are your vehicle of choice! Slap it! Expolode it!
"How much bity or 'splodin' flesh balls you want to shoot??" - "Yes."


FOR BEST QUALITY PRINT, PLEASE READ ALL(!) OF BELOW:

To print the Rukka Buggy, you need time or a resin printer ;-)
I REALLY recommend a layer high of 0.075mm or lower for all parts to get the quality I intended.
Please see the pics, those are all printed in FDM (<=0,075mm)!

I highly recommend it to use tree supports (at least on the crew) - make sure to set the tree support z-distance to a multiple of 2 (layer hight) for optimal removal (keep in mind: layer hight 0.05 (crew) or 0.075mm (buggy))

---------- Over all printing recommendation (FDM) ----------

- Many parts have a flat surface -> face those to the build plate. Print slow (25mm/s)
- Detaild sides / most visible sides should be faced towards the cooling fan.
- Crew should be printed with tree supports, rotated 45¬∞ back (so the face is up). Support Z-distance should be a multiple of 2 to 3 of the layer hight (0.05 - 0.075mm). PRINT SLOW - Outer wall max 25mm/s. You want dem details gooood!

The most difficult parts (actually not the Gobbo Crew...):
- "RuckaBuggy_Rear_02.stl": you need to be super carefull to remove tree supports (they are needed). My test print broke on the bars while removing them. I was able to glue it back on (tip: smooth cracks with a lighter)
- "RuckaBuggy_Front_04.stl": failed 4 times while removing tree supports, combined with other parts. I needed to print this part as a single part with normal supports.

---------- Assembly ----------

If you need instructions - just open all files in 3D Builder or e.g. Meshmixer. There you can look where they go.
Some parts are press fits (e.g. the wheels) you don't need to glue them, unless you print in resin (not tested).
I recommend to "dry fit" the parts with blu tack or a similar reusable putty.


---------- FOLLOWING: ----------

The Gorkabot is a massive armored mech, built as an effigy of a greenskin god! Armed to da teef da Gorkabot krushes all kind of ememys with it's klaw while shredding infantry with hails of bullets from the DAKKA-Storm gun.


In the Gorkabots belly is space for a few greenskins to pop out, if the time is good for some krumpin'!








FOR BEST QUALITY PRINT, PLEASE READ ALL(!) OF BELOW:





To print the Gorkabot, you need time or a resin printer ;-)


I REALLY recommend a layer high of 0.075 or lower for all parts to get the quality I intended.


Please see the pics, those are all printed in FDM (<=0,075mm)!





I tried to keep the need of tree supports low, but I highly recommend it to use them - make sure to set the tree support z-distance to a multiple of 2 (layer hight) for optimal removal (keep in mind: layer hight 0.05 to 0.075(!) )








----------------------------------------------------------------------


-------- EXCEPTIONAL 'fings for this model: ----------


----------------------------------------------------------------------








---------- COMPATIBILITY ----------





Arms and legs should be compatible to my Mega Bots (not testet)





---------- MAIN BODY ----------





"GorkaBot_Belly.stl" prints without tree support! Just use regular supports.


"GorkaBot_Torso.stl" prints without tree support! Just use regular supports. flip the model slightly to the back (see Cura screenshot)


The doors should be printed without supports with a brim (see Cura screenshot)





---------- LEGS ----------





The legs are unique, there is an individual model for the right / left leg. Those are mirrorable / interchangeable if you want.





---------- ARMS----------





The arms should fit 10x4mm magnets (not tested) but also have a ball joint for more posability...





The "GorkaBot_Klaw_Arm_02.stl" should be printed 45¬∞ "floating 1,5mm in the air" see my Cura screenshot - this will give you the best quality result!





---------- Over all printing recommendation! ----------





Many parts have a "flat surface" -> face those to the build plate.


Detaild sides / most visible sides should be faced towards the cooling fan.





---------- Assembly ----------





if you need instructions - just open all files in 3D Builder or e.g. Meshmixer. There you can look where they go








---------- FOLLOWING: ----------

Tersus

(Re-uploaded and revised, May 2021)

This is a simple remix of the Savannah Mister scout hovercraft https://www.sarna.net/wiki/Savannah_Master.

I took the design by LeoCeballos, but wanted it to be more proportional in scale to the old official Savannah Master miniatures produced by Ral Partha (to match my collection).

I expanded the size of the engine at the back of the model to match the proportions of the Ral Partha miniature and re-sized the LeoCeballos model overall to print at the same size as the metal minis.

****************
Please feel free to leave a tip if you like the model and think it is merited - an occasional coffee helps fuel the creativity and effort and sustains morale :)

Check out my Patreon if you want to support the creation of more unique 6mm terrain files: https://www.patreon.com/Shiaic3D

Alternatively, if you want to contribute a little, but still get something for your money, please see my unique designs on Cults 3D. For a small cost (half a coffee), I have a few unique 6mm building creations:

The Krumpin' Mega Bot is a hulking, heavily armored monster! Pistons, welded to powerful close combat weapons, such as the Ripper Klaw deliver enormous hydraulik power to every git or vehicle gettin' to close.
Other than the more commonly Deff Bots and or Kans, Krumpin' Mega Bots are usually armed with high speed rattling weapons of high calibers to kill enemies even before reaching them in close combat! (Or just to make horrible loud noise...)

EDIT: Most Parts are compatible to my Skrappin' Mega Bot
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/skrappin-mega-bot
Build your Bot as you like! :-)

FOR BEST QUALITY PRINT, PLEASE READ ALL(!) OF BELOW:

This is my ambitious model until now!

To print this monster, you need time or a resin printer ;-)
I REALLY recommend a layer high of 0.075 or better for all parts to get the quality I intended, while designing this model - please see the pics, those are printed in FDM

(<=0,075mm)!

I tried to keep the need of tree supports low, but I highly recommend it to use tree supports - make sure to set the tree support z-distance to a multiple of 2 for optimal removal

(keep in mind: layer hight 0.05 to 0.075(!) )

For the Rippa Klaw I added a resin version with "_Resin" in the file name - unlike the FDM versions those don't have a flat bottom. (I have not test printed these files, but they

should be good to go!)

----------------------------------------------------------------------
---------- EXCEPTIONAL 'fings for this model: ----------
----------------------------------------------------------------------


---------- GUN ARM: ----------

THE RATTLA KANNON MAGAZINE IS ROTATABLE IF DONE AS INTENDED!!

For the axies you simply insert usual filament!
If you don't glue the "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_06.stl" to "...05.stl" the "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Mag.stl" is interchangeable - who knows what might be released in future...... ;-)
-> If you don't want this or don't have filament, just glue the parts as wanted.


Assembly as followed: (please see also the last two pics/screenshots!

1. Stick (NOT glue, if you want it to be removable) together:
"MegaBot_RattlerKannon_05" & "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_06", OPTIONAL: "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Barrel.stl"

2. Insert a 1.75mm filament (42mm long - as the answer to all questions, lol) into "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Mag_Back_Spacer.stl", large side first, followed by

"MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Mag".

2.a) Glue on all parts of "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Mag_Back.stl", if you want more realistic details (even if Ork xD).
2.a.note: Warning: print "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Mag_Back.stl" with "brim" 3mm+.
They will, regardless of brim width, fall apart after removing the brim. This is intended so you can glue them bitz more random on the Mag!

3. "Dry fit" (NO glue at first!) all parts

3.a) View the last two pics (Tinkercad screenshots)!

3.b) "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Trigger.stl" to
 "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Mag_Back_Spacer.stl"

3.c) I recommend to glue in "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_TriggerPin.stl" to "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Trigger.stl" first.

3.d) Glue the filament between "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Trigger.stl" & "MegaBot_RattlerKannon_Mag_Back_Spacer.stl"


---------- MAIN BODY ----------

You CAN use two 10x4mm Neodym magnets for the junction "hip <> main hull" to get a rotatable/removable body!

---------- LEGS ----------

The legs are unique, there is a individual model for right / left leg. Those are mirrorable / interchangeable.

---------- Over all printing recommendation! ----------

Many parts have a "flat surface" - face those to the build plate.


---------- FOLLOWING: ----------

Shame less beggin' for some coins for coffein I need doin' stuff like that :-D ;-)

Please consider a tip ....this HIGH detailed model was a work of 100h+ of free time (~50 RL days)! If you do so, I HIGHLY APPRECIATE YOUR GENEROSITY :-) :-):-)

Kind regards,
Tersus

Man dis new Bass Toob I picked up from my noisy boys over in the Six Circles (wiv the usual "discounts") makes you feel like you iz being shanked with every kick. It's the bollox and no mistake. Them 'Neshy boys might look a bit skinny but they know how to turn it right up.

I love the original model by VidovicArts and printed a couple of them, but decided I wanted some more body and weapon options.

I spent an ungodly amount of time in TinkerCAD modifying the original parts to print easier and allow more options.

I figured some other people might like these parts.
Hopefully the original creator doesn't mind I've posted these parts, if you do let me know.

The arms have a flat bit on the shoulder/ball joint, so if you put that flat section on the build plate, you can print them without supports.

Everything else just print how the file is orientated, and use supports on the bottom of the bodies, all the weapons should print without support.

I'll post some photo's when I've done painting some.

3 different 15mm Ork Tanks

These are purely a remix from the 3 modelers I have tagged in the remix section, so all credit to them ! (the are originally grot tanks)

I have ...

- Resized / rescaled some of the guns and detail (or removed / solidified it) to enable print at 15mm and be Ork tanks.
- Made them all into three specific parts for ease of print, Turret, Body and 2 sets of tracks (where they were not already or in different parts).
- Hollowed out and added drain holes for Resin 3D printing.
- Added a recessed hole in the body and turret to allow the use of a 10x2mm magnet so the turret can turn or be swapped.
- Scaled in size overall to 15mm

The models in parts are in the zip files.

The Scroggan Ambush Truck is a common improvised low-tech design found on many back-water planets that typically lack their own dedicated FightMech force or other standing professional militaries. The Scroggan Ambush Truck typically mounts 2x SRM-6s and is designed for a single-shot surprise attack, initiated at close range.

The improvised nature of this method of attack often means that the SRM fire-system is burned out during the initiation, which makes it uncommon for the Scroggan to be able to sustain multiple attacks from the same platform.

To build a Scroggan, a single-salvo SRM pod is usually grafted to whatever cargo moving truck is available locally and then positioned on likely FightMech approaches.

The Scroggan Ambush Truck ambush method was originally used on Thingerse III (in the Deep Periphery) in Jun 3020. In this minor action, a well-equipped force of invading FightMech Pirates was temporarily halted in their advance through the planet's urban capital by several Scroggans. Antonius Scroggan, an officer cadet wash-out from the nearby Taurian Constellation who had settled on the planet, organized several small ambushes that delayed the pirates by at least several days.

Scroggan subsequently blew himself up while wiring in some SRM pods incorrectly, and the Pirates soon claimed Thingerse III - despite the harassing inconvenience imposed by a few remaining trucks and minor damage sustained to several ankle actuators.

In tongue-in-cheek homage to Scroggan, the Pirates afterward referred to this method of singe-shot, low-blow, but largely ineffective ambush as the 'Scroggan Cheap-Shot.'

Death comes in many forms. For this death, it's a ball. Also includes 2 genetic gathering and sampling assistants for free.

For a Devilfish, it's the wrong shape, wrong size, wrong weapon options, and can't technically carry any Kroot, but it's lovely just the same. This was supposed to be a simple joke project that got out of hand. The level of detail isn't the same all over but it's taken up too much of my time and I just need to move on. 

* Comes with open and closed version of the side and back hatches.
* It can either be assembled using 1.75mm filament as alignment pins or 10x2mm magnets.
* Magnets allow for easy breakdown to swap open/closed hatches or easier travel.
* Sides can be printed mirrored for more variety.


You will need heads to complete these models. I recommend purchasing the official box sets for those. Hopefully this will tell THEM that we want more options to add them to our armies. Alternately, if you have a resin printer, another modeler has made these: https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4011591

Check out my printed models for sale: https://www.etsy.com/shop/MasterShaperFelix

My kroot exclusive Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/felixtehcrazy/

Ankylosaurus (meaning ‚Äúfused lizard‚Äù) is a genus of thyreophoran dinosaur. Fossils of Ankylosaurus have been found in geologic formations dating to the very end of the Cretaceous Period, between about 68‚Äì66 million years ago, in western North America, making it among the last of the non-avian dinosaurs. It was named by Barnum Brown in 1908, and the only species classified in the genus is A. magniventris. A handful of specimens have been excavated to date, but a complete skeleton has not been discovered. Though other members of Ankylosauria are represented by more extensive fossil material, Ankylosaurus is often considered the archetypal member of its group.

The front part of the jaws were covered in a beak, with rows of small, leaf-shaped teeth further behind it. It was covered in armor plates, or osteoderms, with bony half-rings covering the neck, and had a large club on the end of its tail. Bones in the skull and other parts of the body were fused, increasing their strength, and this feature is the source of the genus name.

Compared with modern land animals the adult Ankylosaurus was very large. Some scientists have estimated a length of 11 meters (36 ft).[1] Another reconstruction suggests a much smaller size, at 6.25 m (20.5 ft) long, up to 1.5 m (5 ft) wide and about 1.7 m (5.5 ft) high at the hip.[2] Ankylosaurus may have weighed over 6,000 kilograms (13,000 lb), making it one of the heaviest armored dinosaurs yet discovered. The body shape was low-slung and quite wide. It was quadrupedal, with the hind limbs longer than the forelimbs. Although its feet are still unknown, comparisons with other ankylosaurids suggest Ankylosaurus probably had five toes on each foot. The skull was low and triangular in shape, wider than it was long. The largest known skull measures 64.5 centimeters (25 in) long and 74.5 cm (29 in) wide.[4] Their teeth were weaker than ceratopsid and hadrosaurid dinosaurs of the time, so they probably chewed very little.

Parasaurolophus was a hadrosaurid, part of a diverse family of Cretaceous dinosaurs known for their range of bizarre head adornments. This genus is known for its large, elaborate cranial crest, which at its largest forms a long curved tube projecting upwards and back from the skull. Charonosaurus from China, which may have been its closest relative, had a similar skull and potentially a similar crest. Visual recognition of both species and sex, acoustic resonance, and thermoregulation have been proposed as functional explanations for the crest. It is one of the rarer hadrosaurids, known from only a handful of good specimens.

This model is designed for use in Games Workshop's 6mm scale table top wargame, Epic 40,000 (and precessors/successors). They have since abandoned all support for Epic, so I modeled this in Autodesk Inventor for any avid wargamers.

I don't believe there are any official rules for the Minotaur in Epic 40k, but I really like the look of this beast compared to the Basilisk. It adds a bit more variety, or allows the player to field a 30k-themed force.

Epic has been re-released as a titans-only game called Adeptus Titanicus. It is 8mm scale instead of 6mm, so I suggest that anyone wanting to print this for AT scenery or to play 8mm Epic should upscale it by 133%.

Stroganoff made some beautiful Leman Russ models in 6mm for games like Epic. That's great and all, but a 10 Russ company has 9 Main Battle Tanks, and one Vanquisher in NetEA. And then there's the Demolishers you can attach in 3s. What's a gamer to do?

Make them!

Here you will find some variant turrets for Leman Russ chassis tanks. Demolisher, Vanquisher, Punisher, Conqueror, Executioner, Eradicator, Exterminator (come on GeeDubs, those names are just confusing) The Exterminator could double as an Annihilator.

There are two Punisher turrets. A 6 barrel and a 4 barrel. The 4 prints cleaner, but the 6 did not feel as flimsy to me. So your milage may vary there. Could have been my post-processing.

These have been printed on an SLA printer. Some of these items are not going to print well on an FDM printer. The Punisher and Exterminator come to mind. I might edit the Eradicator a little as it has little supports on the side which might be too thin/separated from the main barrel. It won't really affect printing, but might not form well in the process.

This is a Triceratops scan from artec3d.com's gallery. I reduced the mesh from the original and converted the file to STL.

This model requires supports, but the support marks aren't too much of a problem since they're out of sight on the underside and the skin texture also hides them.

I kept the mesh resolution high enough that you should be able to scale this even larger with good results. The size of this model is about 7 inches long by 3 inches high, and I estimate that my Replicator 2 could print it up to 50% larger.
